<div><h3>EDUC 070 - Building Community through Research With </h3>  <hr>This course focuses on methodologies and epistemologies of <em>research with</em>: collaborative research practices that focus on authentic and critical story-telling through words, images, and creative performance. Rather than researching on people in our community, we seek to build relationships that allow us to co-construct research narratives; helping us learn about ourselves and others in how we relate to the world. In order to delve into research <em>with</em>, we draw from literature that challenges deficit-based thinking, explores the rich community and cultural wealth of all people, and interrogates the way systemic racism, hetero-sexism, classism and other inequities shape many of the stories that we have grown up with.<br><br><strong>Course Designation/Attribute:</strong> FA<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Fall<br><br></div>		</td>
